{"id": "28061", "post": "<div class=\"post-28061 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-hacked tag-leaks tag-mcafee tag-security tag-t-mobile\" id=\"post-28061\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/t-mobile-leaks-almost-50-million-peoples-ssns-and-drivers-licenses/\" rel=\"bookmark\">T-Mobile Leaks Almost 50 Million People\u2019s SSNs and Driver\u2019s Licenses</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/hacked/\" rel=\"tag\">Hacked</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/leaks/\" rel=\"tag\">leaks</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/mcafee/\" rel=\"tag\">mcafee</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/security/\" rel=\"tag\">Security</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/t-mobile/\" rel=\"tag\">t-mobile</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> August 19, 2021 @ 12:00 pm, by raindog308</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/t-mobile.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-28062 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/t-mobile.jpg\" alt=\"T-Mobile Logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" align=\"right\" hspace=\"20\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/t-mobile.jpg 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/t-mobile-150x150.jpg 150w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/t-mobile.jpg 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/t-mobile-150x150.jpg 150w\" data-was-processed=\"true\">T-Mobile <a href=\"https://investor.t-mobile.com/news-and-events/t-mobile-us-press-releases/press-release-details/2021/T-Mobile-Shares-Additional-Information-Regarding-Ongoing-Cyberattack-Investigation/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"T-Mobile Press Release\">announced on Wednesday</a> that a \u201ca bad actor had compromised T-Mobile systems\u201d:</p><p><em>\u201cSome of the data accessed did include customers\u2019 first and last names, date of birth, SSN, and driver\u2019s license/ID information for a subset of current and former postpay customers and prospective T-Mobile customers.</em></p><p><em>\u201cOur preliminary analysis is that approximately 7.8 million current T-Mobile postpaid customer accounts\u2019 information appears to be contained in the stolen files, as well as just over 40 million records of former or prospective customers who had previously applied for credit with T-Mobile.\u201d</em></p><p>If these are all US residents, that means about 1 in 6 Americans is affected.</p><p>Of course, T-mobile takes \u201ccustomers\u2019 protection very seriously\u201d and is working \u201caround the clock on this forensic investigation\u201d in concert with \u201cworld-leading cybersecurity experts\u201d etcetera etcetera.&nbsp; Those affected can expect notification from T-mobile, 2 years of McAfee\u2019s ID Theft Protection Service, and future identity theft headaches.</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/report-reveals-cpanel-whm-suffers-multiple-vulnerabilities/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=